# Skeleton loading

## When to use skeletons

- Any page or section that fetches data (`useQuery`, `useGet*`) should show a skeleton while `isLoading` — never an empty layout or full-page spinner unless the action is a button submit.
- Skeleton shape must **match the loaded layout** (same columns, card count, sidebar width) to avoid layout shift.

## Shared components

Import from `@/components/skeletons`:

| UI pattern | Component |
|------------|-----------|
| Page title + subtitle (+ action) | `PageHeaderSkeleton` |
| Create/edit form page | `FormPageSkeleton` (`layout: 'two-column' \| 'single'`, `sections`) |
| Stat / metric cards | `SummaryCardSkeleton` or `SummaryCardsSkeleton` |
| Full list page (no DataTable yet) | `TableListSkeleton` |
| Paginated table inside DataTable | pass `isLoading` to `DataTable` (built-in row skeletons) |

## Styling

- Base primitive: `Skeleton` from `@/components/ui/skeleton`
- Use Crimson Forge tokens: `rounded-sm`, `ring-1 ring-primary/10`, `bg-card` on card-shaped placeholders
- For small inline panels (gallery grid, attribute list), local skeleton grids are OK — reuse `rounded-sm` sizing from existing patterns in `product-media-sidebar.tsx`

## Patterns

```tsx
// Page-level fetch
if (isLoading) return <FormPageSkeleton layout="two-column" sections={5} />;

// Dashboard / stats
if (isLoading) return (
  <div className="space-y-6">
    <PageHeaderSkeleton showAction />
    <SummaryCardsSkeleton count={4} columns={4} />
  </div>
);

// Table via DataTable — prefer isLoading prop, not a separate page skeleton
<DataTable isLoading={isLoading} ... />
```

## Do not

- Add one-off page skeletons with raw `<Skeleton className="h-96" />` blocks when a shared component fits
- Show "Loading..." text alone without a skeleton placeholder for layout-heavy views
- Block entire app with spinners when a section-level skeleton suffices

## Domain-specific composites

- Dashboard: keep `DashboardSkeleton` composed from shared skeletons + chart placeholders
- New domains (orders, customers): compose from `PageHeaderSkeleton` + `TableListSkeleton` or `SummaryCardsSkeleton` before creating domain-only skeleton files
